    "text": "[@PinkMoff](@LMkiSqWlqiGPsGErLq5PphsduuN4d5tkmUO0+lcgBlM=.ed25519) \n\nSo usually the message format is:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"key\": \"%abc.sha256\",\n  \"value\": {\n    \"previous\": \"%XphMUkWQtomKjXQvFGfsGYpt69sgEY7Y4Vou9cEuJho=.sha256\",\n    \"author\": \"@FCX/tsDLpubCPKKfIrw4gc+SQkHcaD17s7GI6i/ziWY=.ed25519\",\n    \"sequence\": 2,\n    \"timestamp\": 1514517078157,\n    \"hash\": \"sha256\",\n    \"content\": {\n      \"type\": \"post\",\n      \"text\": \"First post!\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nInstead, I was thinking something like:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"key\": \"%abc.sha256\",\n  \"value\": {\n    \"previous\": \"%XphMUkWQtomKjXQvFGfsGYpt69sgEY7Y4Vou9cEuJho=.sha256\",\n    \"author\": \"@FCX/tsDLpubCPKKfIrw4gc+SQkHcaD17s7GI6i/ziWY=.ed25519\",\n    \"sequence\": 2,\n    \"timestamp\": 1514517078157,\n    \"hash\": \"sha256\",\n    \"content\": [{\n      \"type\": \"post\",\n      \"text\": \"First post!\"\n    }, {\n      \"type\": \"post\",\n      \"text\": \"Second post!\"\n    }, {\n      \"type\": \"something-else\",\n      \"foo\": \"bar\"\n    }]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nInstead of writing three messages you could put three message objects in one message, so you'd just need a way to reference them. I'd imagine you could use a system like [scoped IPv6 addresses](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IPv6_address#Scoped_literal_IPv6_addresses) where `%abc.sha256` references the entire message and `%abc.sha256` but you'd reference the message objects as:\n\n- `%abc.sha256%0`\n- `%abc.sha256%1`\n- `%abc.sha256%2`\n\nI'm not convinced that this is a *good* idea, but it's an idea.",
